The paper discusses a lensless compressive imaging architecture that uses compressive sensing to capture images in a compressed form of compressive measurements. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper analyzes the signal to noise ratio (SNR) in the lensless compressive imaging architecture, which could fall under the Optimization and Control (cs.OH) or Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category, as it deals with analyzing and processing signals.
